# SEO Article Project Rules

## Architecture (5 layers, top-down only)
core/ -> adapters/ -> modules/ -> plugins/ -> apps/
Route Handler <= 10 lines. All logic in modules/*.service.ts.
modules/ NEVER imports Next.js.
new PrismaClient() only in lib/prisma.ts.

## Key files
- `plugins/seo-article-express/prompt.ts` — buildSystemPrompt (63KB, 22 dynamic blocks)
- `modules/seo/steps/step-1-2-brief.ts` — SEO_TABLE + brief generation
- `modules/seo/steps/step-7-assembly.ts` — wrapWithInlineStyles + metadata
- `modules/seo/steps/step-6-images.ts` — image generation, base64 in figure tags
- `components/seo-article/ScreenResult.tsx` — article preview (dangerouslySetInnerHTML)
- `components/seo-article/ExportPanel.tsx` — copy/download with transformForDzen/transformForTilda
- `lib/seo-article/export.ts` — copyArticle, downloadHTML, downloadDOCX

## Pipeline data flow
draft(article_html) -> seo_audit -> content_analysis -> ai_detect_revisions(article_html) -> targeted_rewrite(article_html) -> images(article_html) -> assembly(article_html)

## Known issues (TODO)
- No HTML sanitization between pipeline steps — LLM may add style/div/span
- wrapWithInlineStyles in assembly can double style attributes if LLM already added them
- Images inserted as base64 data URI in img src — breaks Dzen/Word export, makes HTML huge
- article_docx_base64 = '' (not implemented)
- No retry on draft length — if LLM generates 25% less than target, only warning

## HTML rules
- Allowed tags: h1 h2 h3 p blockquote ul ol li a img strong em figure figcaption cite nav
- Forbidden tags: h4 h5 h6 div span section article header footer main (except article wrapper in assembly)
- style attributes are ONLY added by wrapWithInlineStyles in step-7-assembly

## Agent behavior
- Before editing: read ONLY the relevant function, not the whole file
- Make replacements directly, no verbose analysis in response text
- Never re-read a file already read in this session
- For string replacements: skip full file reads, use grep to find anchor
- No hardcoded colors in components — use CSS variables from tokens.css
- No hardcoded years in prompt examples — use relative time or dynamic currentYear

## SEO_TABLE reference (step-1-2-brief.ts)
charCount ranges: 6000/8000/10000/12000/14000/16000/18000/20000
Columns: minH2 maxH2 minH3Total maxH3Total hasConclusion hasFaq maxFaq

## Models config (from DB tools.config.models)
brief/draft/ai_detect/revisions/assembly: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4
moderation/moderation_headings/image_prompt: google/gemini-2.5-flash
image_gen: google/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview